---
// 12. FAQ — accordion (toggled in main.ts).
---
<section class="faq" id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section__title" data-i18n="faq.title">Common questions</h2>
    <div class="faq__list">
      <div class="faq__item is-open">
        <button class="faq__q" data-i18n="faq.q-weak-english">Will it work if my English is weak?<svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4"/></svg></button>
        <div class="faq__a"><p data-i18n="faq.a-weak-english">Yes — that's exactly what it's built for. Questions, terms, and explanations come with parallel translation and audio in your language, so you grasp the material right away, even while your English is still growing.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <button class="faq__q" data-i18n="faq.q-need-real-estate">Do I need to know real estate already?<svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4"/></svg></button>
        <div class="faq__a"><p data-i18n="faq.a-need-real-estate">No. The course is designed for beginners: you learn the subject from scratch, and the language layer removes the English barrier — no prior real estate experience required.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <button class="faq__q" data-i18n="faq.q-which-exam">Which exam does this prepare me for?<svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4"/></svg></button>
        <div class="faq__a"><p data-i18n="faq.a-which-exam">The Florida real estate license exam (Sales Associate). We cover both portions — the national portion and Florida law — across every section of the current outline.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <button class="faq__q" data-i18n="faq.q-languages">Which languages have translation and audio?<svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4"/></svg></button>
        <div class="faq__a"><p data-i18n="faq.a-languages">10 of them: Spanish, Portuguese (Brazilian), Haitian Creole, Russian, French, German, Italian, Chinese (Mandarin), Arabic, and Tagalog.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <button class="faq__q" data-i18n="faq.q-tests-flashcards">Is it just tests and flashcards?<svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4"/></svg></button>
        <div class="faq__a"><p data-i18n="faq.a-tests-flashcards">No: an interactive textbook with audio, term flashcards, adaptive tests with explanations, spaced repetition, and exam math made simple — all in one app, with translation built into every tool.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <button class="faq__q" data-i18n="faq.q-vs-regular-prep">How is this different from regular exam prep?<svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4"/></svg></button>
        <div class="faq__a"><p data-i18n="faq.a-vs-regular-prep">Regular prep is English-only and one-size-fits-all. Here, translation, audio, and spaced repetition are built into every piece of material so language doesn't cost you points, while adaptive tests take the shortest path — closing exactly your gaps.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <button class="faq__q" data-i18n="faq.q-payment">How does payment work?<svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4"/></svg></button>
        <div class="faq__a"><p data-i18n="faq.a-payment">A one-time payment, no auto-renewal. You choose your access period — a week, a month, or three — and renew if you'd like. There's a 7-day money-back guarantee.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
